d Working.";i:41;s:86:"A remote-control garage-door opener is a handy little electronic device that makes it.";i:42;s:60:"A remote will not work if there is no power at the receiver.";i:43;s:118:"Check for Blocked Safety Sensors The safety sensors are located near the bottom rear corners of the garage door track.";i:44;s:166:"If all Remotes have stopped working then it is most likely a problem with your Garage Door Motor you will need to contact a Local Garage Door Serviceman in your area.";i:45;s:86:"If it is just one Remote not working this points towards the Remote being the problem.";i:46;s:139:"After going through our checklist and finding your Garage Door Remote still will not work then your best option would be to purchase a new.";}}